Three men accused of murdering former ANCYL secretary-general and later Umzimkhulu councillor, Sindiso Magaqa are out on bail. The trio, Mbulelo Mpofana, Sibonelo Myeza, and Mlungisi Ncalane were granted bail of R5000 each. According to the KwaZulu-Natal provincial National prosecuting Authority (NPA), they appeared at the Ixopo Magistrates’ Court on Tuesday. Natasha Ramkisson-Kara, NPA’s Regional Spokesperson said the men were granted bail following their bail application on new facts. Ramkisson-Kara said the trio, together with their co-accused Sibusiso Ncengwa, are charged with the murder of Sindiso Magaqa who was shot and killed in uMzimkhulu in July 2017. She said their bail conditions are to surrender their passports to the investigating Officer, report bi-weekly to a police station in their area, they must not enter the area of uMzimkhulu for the duration that this matter is in court and they do not interfere with State witnesses She said the matter returns to court on July 18. She added that the State is considering an appeal of the ruling which led to the accused being released on bail.